  "title": "ISic000551. I.Sicily inscription 000551",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Giorgia Capra</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Paconio · Clodiano\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Paconio\">Paconio</span> · <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Clodiano\">Clodiano</span></span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>patrono · bene <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>merenti <br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>ex · aere · conlato </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Giorgia Capra</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Paconio · Clodiano\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Paconio\">PACONIO</span>·<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Clodiano\">CLODIANO</span></span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>PATRONO·BENE<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>MERENTI<br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>EX·AERE·CONLATO</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text of CIL</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1030-5679\">Giorgia Capra</a></p>  <p>To Paconius Clodianus, most deserving patron, (gift) from communally collected money.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>Italian translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1030-5679\">Giorgia Capra</a></p>  <p>A Paconius Clodianus, meritevole patrono, (dono) finanziato con denaro pubblico.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Mommsen rightly notes that there is a very close overlap between this text and the slightly fuller one recorded at Marsala in CIL 10.7238, such that it is possible that these are corrupted records of the same original inscription</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li></li><li> Gualtherus 1624 75 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388</a>  </li><li> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 223 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931</a>  </li><li> Mommsen 1883 <a href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/CILv10pII1883\" target=\"_blank\">7294</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  </div>",
